 type="inclusive">1868-1882</unitdate><container id="aspace_b8a91a4299a3f1d242fcd2a06e68ba9c" label="Mixed Materials [31924079236901]" type="box">1</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_b03a35087a14d2e9b9e1318f648d513a" level="item"><did><unittitle>Chenango County</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1869/1882" type="inclusive">1869-1882</unitdate><container id="aspace_29c97ba6f3e4bc571f201515d2cb835a" label="Mixed Materials [31924079236901]" type="box">1</container></did></c02></c01><c01 id="aspace_3218cf616d0fb7173bde25508ccaf2d1" level="file"><did><unittitle>Diaries, 14 volumes 1890-1893 , 1896 ,</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1890/1893" type="inclusive">1890-1893</unitdate><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1896/1896">1896</unitdate><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1898/1906" type="inclusive">1898-1906</unitdate><container id="aspace_17a5e8b882e4a06fd4285ca2ad3d3ebf" label="Mixed Materials [31924079236927]" type="box">2</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_cf5b803e6df31fe7fe7e67e36bf112b6"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Daily entries include brief weather report and any unusual occurence along the right of way (e.g. man killed by engine, wreckers working at some particular spot, etc.) Note: These and ones listed below used by dispatchers at Norwich controlling Northern Division trains.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_ea33d3a6612b44c8359db95df0509c94" level="file"><did><unittitle>19 notebooks used as engineer's survey books.</unittitle><container id="aspace_c585ee99fc3e43724727dcb66471866b" label="Mixed Materials [31924079236927]" type="box">2</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_0e13b8675d78c5a37a23aa3d8ed2a21d"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Notebooks contain varied information - abutment descriptions, location sites photographed, surveying information, etc. Note: c. 1910, when line was being improved ...locates exactly and gives specifications for track and structures.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_8cf495ce8f747b22e82e699870aebb22" level="file"><did><unittitle>Notices - 2-12, 14-16.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1948/1956" type="inclusive">1948-1956</unitdate><container id="aspace_168476b389bdd8252cff6496904ddc5f" label="Mixed Materials [31924079236935]" type="box">3</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_40929f528be830d0eee2a1431be554ff"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Official notices pertaining to schedule changes, changes in routing, etc. Also General Order #387, Rev. no. 1, July 1, 1952</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_ee724b1527d809c03591be5c1b226d55" level="file"><did><unittitle>Timetable - N. 75 effective Sunday Apr. 25, 1954 Eastern Standard Time.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1954-04-25/1954-04-25">Apr. 25, 1954</unitdate><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1954/1954">1954</unitdate><container id="aspace_c5feb0d1059d9e962e8cc1e91eaf7e6c" label="Mixed Materials [31924079236935]" type="box">3</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_4951e202e0b24b51212078cbaf809273" level="file"><did><unittitle>"Analysis of Operations of the Rutland Railway Corporation as compared with the New York, Ontario, and Western Railway prepared by Lewis D. Freeman, trustee, N.Y., O. &amp; W. Railway." 21 pp. Middletown, N.Y.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1956-05-14/1956-05-14">May 14, 1956</unitdate><container id="aspace_2b9fd3a7ae7c6980a58921aebc546dfc" label="Mixed Materials [31924079236935]" type="box">3</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_d75ba87c9e33f6f65f09e7776e1846b8" level="file"><did><unittitle>Diaries, 23 volumes.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1907/1929" type="inclusive">1907-1929</unitdate><container id="aspace_d194217353208d2732ef202c452b052a" label="Mixed Materials [31924079236935]" type="box">3</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_4094b2e4b49173f14c334157429d1c77" level="